    "created_at": "2015-09-23T16:33:30Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-23T16:43:38Z",
    "body": "Using files without a synchronization mechanism or locks, could lead to race conditions and data corruption. This might not be an issue, depending on access patterns and the type of data, but I think you would be better off using some caching or ipc modules from npm. For example:\n- [node-shared-cache](https://www.npmjs.com/package/node-shared-cache)\n- [node-ipc](https://www.npmjs.com/package/node-ipc)\n- [ipc-shared](https://www.npmjs.com/package/ipc-shared)\n"
  },
